<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><?xml-stylesheet href="/pretty-feed-v3.xsl" type="text/xsl"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Haiku by Pranshu Gaba</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/tags/haiku/</link><description/><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><copyright>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.</copyright><lastBuildDate>Wed, 28 May 2025 17:43:17 +0530</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://pranshugaba.com/tags/haiku/icon.png</url></image><atom:link href="https://pranshugaba.com/tags/haiku/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>white horse</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/white-horse/</link><pubDate>Mon, 23 Oct 2023 19:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/white-horse/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/white-horse/white-horse-featured_hu_f99a2c60b4872429.jpg"  /><p>amidst the garbage dump<br>
beside the mangroves one finds<br>
a majestic white horse</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>barcode</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/barcode/</link><pubDate>Sat, 14 Oct 2023 20:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/barcode/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/barcode/barcode_featured_hu_c555a3eaad3466a2.webp"  /><p>telephone wires<br>
information transmission &mdash;<br>
barcode in the sky</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>breakdown</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/breakdown/</link><pubDate>Thu, 11 May 2023 18:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/breakdown/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/breakdown/breakdown_featured_hu_7ca20ee496d57401.webp"  /><p>yellow jcb<br>
amidst the bricky rubble<br>
causes a breakdown</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>high</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/high/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Jun 2022 23:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/high/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/high/high_featured_hu_c02280486a4fa7a9.jpg"  /><p>white plane flies high<br>
against a sky so bright &mdash;<br>
it appears black</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>mlem</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mlem/</link><pubDate>Thu, 28 Apr 2022 17:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mlem/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mlem/mlem_featured_hu_9072b2ac29b5dbc1.jpg"  /><p>golden cat<br>
on a red suitcase &mdash;<br>
does a mlem</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>sunset</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sunset/</link><pubDate>Mon, 04 Apr 2022 05:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sunset/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sunset/sunset_featured_hu_80a1e018c9a3cee0.jpg"  /><p>the sun is<br>
setting in the sky &ndash;<br>
say bye-bye</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>μάραθον</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/marathon/</link><pubDate>Fri, 04 Feb 2022 02:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/marathon/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/marathon/marathon_featured_hu_876742f876d180ab.jpg"  /><p>handful of seeds<br>
tossed in a flowerpot &mdash;<br>
<em>marathon</em><sup id="fnref:1"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1</a></sup></p>
<p> </p>
<div class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes">
<hr>
<ol>
<li id="fn:1">
<p>Marathon (<em>μάραθον</em>) is Greek for a field of fennels.&#160;<a href="#fnref:1" class="footnote-backref" role="doc-backlink">&#x21a9;&#xfe0e;</a></p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
]]></description></item><item><title>blue</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/blue/</link><pubDate>Tue, 17 Aug 2021 23:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/blue/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/blue/blue_featured_hu_e2d030127b93fc0f.jpg"  /><p>i&rsquo;m afraid<br>
the esteemed car<br>
just blue itself</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>McSwirl</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mcswirl/</link><pubDate>Wed, 13 Jan 2021 13:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mcswirl/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mcswirl/mcswirl_featured_hu_970296887a958b9b.jpg"  /><p>vanilla McSwirl<br>
thrown out of a moving car &mdash;<br>
even crows didn&rsquo;t eat it</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>debris</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/debris/</link><pubDate>Sat, 28 Nov 2020 23:46:01 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/debris/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/debris/debris_featured_hu_332388925b02aa72.jpg"  /><p>among debris<br>
beside the covered statue &mdash;<br>
news is read</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>masks</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/masks/</link><pubDate>Wed, 25 Nov 2020 17:15:13 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/masks/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/masks/masks_featured_hu_815b4b30bd3d2d39.jpg"  /><p>a pandemic so severe<br>
everyone wears masks &mdash;<br>
even mannequins</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>ocean</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ocean/</link><pubDate>Tue, 27 Oct 2020 13:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ocean/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ocean/ocean_featured_hu_516c5e0beeec0bee.jpg"  /><p>an ocean of knowledge<br>
and adventures galore&mdash;<br>
sold by weight</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>ambulance</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ambulance/</link><pubDate>Wed, 30 Sep 2020 13:30:46 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ambulance/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/ambulance/ambulance_featured_hu_2864614b874acb1a.jpg"  /><p>rush hour traffic<br>
lights blinking red and blue &mdash;<br>
an ambulance whizzes by</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>crossing</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/crossing/</link><pubDate>Mon, 17 Aug 2020 20:54:24 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/crossing/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/crossing/crossing_featured_hu_90ef7cf1f1ac58e6.jpeg"  /><p>look left and right<br>
before crossing the road &mdash;<br>
and railway tracks</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>spider</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spider/</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Aug 2020 15:09:40 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spider/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spider/spider_featured_hu_d614fc7f5ddaf9a9.jpg"  /><p>bright blue dots<br>
glowing in the dark &mdash;<br>
radioactive spider</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>sofa</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sofa/</link><pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2019 14:04:32 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sofa/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/sofa/sofa_featured_hu_d519df9ec0930730.jpeg"  /><p>covered in cardboard<br>
a sofa waiting outside —<br>
it’s about to rain</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>equines</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/equines/</link><pubDate>Sat, 19 Oct 2019 18:32:12 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/equines/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/equines/equines_featured_hu_5d6a19c6376a8928.jpg"  /><p>two donkeys munch grass<br>
on a cloudy sunny day &mdash;<br>
outside a book fair</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>tributaries</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/tributaries/</link><pubDate>Sun, 28 Jul 2019 21:46:56 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/tributaries/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/tributaries/tributaries_featured_hu_59525dbe26c7b6fe.jpeg"  /><p>a river and its<br>
tributaries aren’t unlike<br>
trees and their branches</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>beads</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beads/</link><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jul 2019 18:44:50 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beads/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beads/beads_featured_hu_d7503e4894edca66.jpg"  /><p>cold rainy morning &mdash;<br>
beads of glass hang like an<br>
ornate chandelier</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>vines</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/vines/</link><pubDate>Sat, 20 Jul 2019 16:35:31 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/vines/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/vines/vines_featured_hu_8849617509d7270a.jpeg"  /><p>in the rainy months,<br>
the railway crossing sign dons<br>
a coat of green vines</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>pink</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/pink/</link><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jul 2019 16:40:33 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/pink/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/pink/pink_featured_hu_d9a1bff4ca9741d7.jpeg"  /><p>a blossom of pink<br>
dainty carpet on the ground<br>
yet swept off the road</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>fire</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/fire/</link><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jul 2019 21:43:52 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/fire/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/fire/fire_featured_hu_8f36f35e1244901a.jpeg"  /><p>fire burning bright —<br>
leaving nothing behind but<br>
dim amber embers</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>flames</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/flames/</link><pubDate>Sun, 14 Jul 2019 21:19:45 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/flames/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/flames/flames_featured_hu_85189e42b8f71b5e.jpeg"  /><p>orange flames above —<br>
providing cool respite from<br>
the sweltering sun</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>streaks</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/streaks/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jul 2019 22:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/streaks/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/streaks/streaks_featured_hu_d8d0a5636db4ecea.jpeg"  /><p>blazing streaks of light &mdash;<br>
drawing beautiful patterns<br>
with long exposure</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>grey water</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/grey-water/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jul 2019 18:27:42 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/grey-water/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/grey-water/grey-water_featured_hu_e931b7172ee84583.jpg"  /><p>a new day begins &mdash;<br>
above the grey water grows<br>
a flower rainbow</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>mirror world</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mirror-world/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jul 2019 22:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mirror-world/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/mirror-world/mirror-world_featured_hu_61eb281a36dc6771.jpeg"  /><p>in the mirror world &mdash;<br>
contrariwise, the sun sets<br>
in the eastern sky</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>beyond</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beyond/</link><pubDate>Sun, 07 Jul 2019 12:42:24 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beyond/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/beyond/beyond_featured_hu_76530ee2e750bee8.jpeg"  /><p>summer afternoon —<br>
do you know what lies beyond?<br>
white green blue and brown</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>purple</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/purple/</link><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jul 2019 18:19:52 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/purple/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/purple/purple_featured_hu_7ec7c9ca30e95326.jpg"  /><p>purple twilight<br>
branches reach for the sky &mdash;<br>
infinite fractals</p>
]]></description></item><item><title>spring</title><link>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spring/</link><pubDate>Fri, 08 Feb 2019 21:30:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spring/</guid><description>
<![CDATA[<img src="https://pranshugaba.com/poems/spring/spring_featured_hu_377ff45a3c53f5d1.jpg"  /><p>spring begins &mdash;<br>
honeybees gather nectar<br>
from vibrant flowers</p>
]]></description></item></channel></rss>